CONTRIBUTOR LICENSE AGREEMENT (CLA)
(Full Assignment + Broad Rights + Zero-Trust Contribution Model)

Version 1.0
This Contributor License Agreement (“Agreement”) is entered into by and between:
Repository Owner (“Owner”): [Insert Legal Name or Entity of Owner]
Contributor (“You”): The individual or entity submitting code, documentation, or other
contributions (“Contribution”) to any repository owned or controlled by the Owner,
including repositories hosted on GitHub or any successor platform.
By submitting a Contribution, You agree to the terms of this Agreement.

1. DEFINITIONS

1.1 “Contribution” means any code, documentation, design, configuration, bug report,
feature request, or other material submitted to the Owner’s repositories.

1.2 “Submission” means any form of delivery of a Contribution, including pull requests,
commits, issues, patches, or emails.

1.3 “Owner Materials” means all existing and future materials in repositories controlled
by the Owner.

2. ZERO-TRUST CONTRIBUTION MODEL

2.1 This Agreement operates under a Zero-Trust Contribution Model, meaning:
No Contribution is accepted, trusted, or integrated by default.
No rights, permissions, or licenses are granted by implication.
All Contributions are treated as untrusted until explicitly accepted by the Owner.

2.2 Submission of a Contribution does not guarantee acceptance, review, or inclusion.

2.3 The Owner may reject or discard any Contribution at their sole discretion.

3. ASSIGNMENT OF RIGHTS

3.1 Full Transfer of Ownership
To the maximum extent permitted by law, You hereby irrevocably and permanently assign,
transfer, and convey to the Owner all right, title, and interest worldwide in and to the
Contribution, including:
Copyright
Patent rights (if applicable)
Trade secrets
Database rights
Moral rights (to the extent transferable)
Any other intellectual property rights

3.2 This assignment includes all past, present, and future rights arising from the
Contribution.

3.3 If any portion of this assignment is deemed invalid under applicable law, You instead
grant the Owner an exclusive, perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, royalty-free, transferable,
sublicensable license with equivalent scope.

4. BROAD LICENSE BACK TO OWNER
To the extent any rights are not fully assigned under Section 3, You grant the Owner:
A perpetual
Irrevocable
Worldwide
Royalty-free
Fully sublicensable
Transferable
license to:
a. Use, reproduce, modify, adapt, and distribute the Contribution
b. Incorporate the Contribution into proprietary or open-source works
c. Create derivative works
d. Commercially exploit the Contribution in any form
e. Relicense the Contribution under any terms the Owner chooses

5. CONTRIBUTOR REPRESENTATIONS
You represent and warrant that:

5.1 You have the legal right to make the Contribution.

5.2 The Contribution is your original work or you have obtained all necessary permissions.

5.3 The Contribution does not infringe any third-party rights.

5.4 You are not transferring any rights that are subject to restrictions preventing
assignment to the Owner.
6. NO RETAINED RIGHTS BY CONTRIBUTOR

6.1 Except for moral rights that cannot be waived under applicable law, You retain no
ownership interest in the Contribution once submitted.

6.2 You waive any right to:
Compensation
Attribution (unless the Owner chooses otherwise)
Approval of use, modification, or distribution

7. RELICENSING AND COMMERCIAL USE

7.1 The Owner may:
Relicense Contributions at any time, under any license (including proprietary licenses)
Sell, distribute, or commercialize Contributions
Incorporate Contributions into closed-source or proprietary systems
Use Contributions in SaaS, enterprise, or commercial products

7.2 No royalties or compensation shall be owed to the Contributor.

8. TRADEMARKS & SERVICE MARKS

8.1 All trademarks, service marks, branding, and project identity associated with the
repositories are exclusively owned and controlled by the Owner.

8.2 No license is granted to use such marks except with explicit written permission.

9. CONTRIBUTOR ACKNOWLEDGEMENT
By submitting a Contribution, You acknowledge and agree that:
You are voluntarily transferring rights under this Agreement
You understand this Agreement is legally binding
You understand this Agreement may be enforced globally
You are not relying on any external representations
10. GOVERNING LAW

This Agreement shall be governed by and interpreted under the laws of the jurisdiction
chosen by the Owner, without regard to conflict of law principles.

11. ENTIRE AGREEMENT
This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties regarding
Contributions and supersedes any prior understandings.
